text: So my guess is that the plague/zombie outbreak happened when Mr. and Mrs. Bennet were young adults (or at least when Elizabeth and her sisters were very young), which forces/gives enough time for the rules of whatever society is left to change throughout Elizabeth's and Darcy's childhoods and by the time they're adults. Maybe the rules are that every single person must know how to fight, and always be prepared if/when they are faced with an undead. Even during parties, which could be their way of living instead of just surviving. And when a girl gets married, she is probably expected to give up her responsibility of battle in exchange for raising, teaching, and protecting whatever children she bears (repopulating the human race and making sure they live to be strong adults and all that jazz). I'm not saying that the movie will be good, I'm just saying that the story has the potential to not be ridicules. I'd like to see how the society and people of old England would be transformed when faced/raised with the daily adversity of the zombie apocalypse.
